Section : Test Strategy (30) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :

1.  For language selection in testing: The default test is EN,if the project only sold in CN, please select CN at FVT/SIT phase. 


 
2. Record the results to Performance Test Report which can download from the attachments of PFA000.

3. When record the results to CER test report, please ask to TPM/PPA for which SPEC your project should be followed.
4. For the project supported Win10 S, you can run the test on normal OS.
 
Section : Prepare (30) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
1. Refresh the latest BIOS and load BIOS to the default value.
2. Preload the latest system and OOBE.
Note: Do not include "Space" in user's name.
3. Verify the DUT has no problem with drivers/devices in device manager.
Investigate and fix all devices with a "!" in device manager.
4. Connect internet by WI-FI.
5. Check Windows Update, and install all drivers and Windows updates.

6. Check for update of the default Anti-virus(MacAfee) software and perform a full scan.

7. Power mode is default (Balanced).

8. Download the latest Test Tools from "Download Case Tools". 

9.Unzip Prep Tool to C driver.

10.Run "Runme.bat " as Administrator.

11.Waitting System will be auto reboot.

System will be auto reboot.

12.Delete "data" in "C:\"
 
Section : Fast startup performance test (30) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :

1. Unzip Fast startup performance test tool to C driver

2. Open the file, and run "RunJob.bat" as Administrator.

3. When show "Assessment Launcher - New job1", click the "Run job on this computer" to go on.

4. Ensure the "Important information about running this job", below it, there have no warning.

5. Click "Start" to begin the test.

6. When completely and run "Check result.bat" as Administrator.

7. When show "windows assessment Console", click "Options"->click "Open results".

8. When popup "Select Results" interface, click "Import".

9. When show "Import Results", click "Browse" and select the results folder->click "Next".

10.When show "Import results completed successfully", click "Finish".

11.Select imported results in "Select Results" interface, and click "Open".

12.When results appear, record the result to CER test report.

12.1 Fast Startup: Total Boot[Excluding BIOS] Time(s)

Make sure the result meet the SPEC.

12.2 Fast Startup: Shutdown Time(s)

Make sure the result meet the SPEC.

12.3 Fast Startup: Bios Initialization Time(s)

Make sure the result meet the SPEC.

Section : Batterylife Edge Web Browsing (60) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :

Note: This item only Win11 OS or later version and your project in NPI need to test.


You should keep the network environment stable before test.


 


1、You can download the tool in attachment to check the battery whether meet the requirement of battery life test.
    a. Download the tool from the attachment.
    b. Unzip the tool package.
    c. Double click "checkBatteryStatus.cmd".
    d. The result will be shown. If not meet, you should replace the battery.


2、Make sure battery is fully charged to 100% before run this test.

1. Unzip "data" test tool to C driver.

3. Set the brightness as close to 150 nits as possible with the nits meter.


-In Settings > System > Display, disable “Change brightness automatically when lighting changes” if the setting is available


-In Settings > System > Display > “Change brightness based on content” change the setting to off if enabled by default then reenable the feature if and only if the feature was turned on by default after the brightness % was set to 150 nits.


If these settings do not show in Window Settings check Intel DPST (OPST for OLED)/ AMD Vari-Bright, in their display utility. (QC CABL is set by Windows Settings). If AMD Vari-Bright or Intel DPST is enabled by default, turn these features off before taking the brightness measurement, then reenable them after the brightness percentage has been calibrated. Click "Change advanced power settings" Settings > System > Display > Brightness. Take note of that percentage with "On Battery" and set the percentage of the value under "Plugged in" to the same percentage as the one next to On Battery.

4. Set volume of speaker to 15%.

5. Turn off keyboard backlight if the machine supported.

6.You will need a Microsoft Account outlook.com test account for this scenario and not a corporate M365 account. The test account must be provisioned with password only (no PIN, Hello, etc.) for automation purposes.Put your outlook.com test MSA credentials in C:\data\asmt\Assessment2\scenarios parameters.abl.credentials.json. Set the Outlook language to English.


 


Outlooks setting



If the following reactions do not occur, you can ignore them


a.Under certain circumstances it’s possible that a pop-out window for syncing Edge account break automation upon first execution of the workload. Before running packages, make sure to remove the Edge profile manually via Settings page to avoid this problem


b.Go to Accounts > Email & accounts to remove all accounts within Accounts used by other apps.


c.If your device first time goes through OOBE, you might see below pop-out window on Edge. Please click “No, thanks” manually to skip it.

7. Open the folder C:\data\Asmt, and run RunJobABLTraining.cmd as Administrator.

If fail,please check  your setting and try run again.

8. Ensure no warnings under the "Important information about running this job"  

9. When show "Assessment Launcher - New job1", click the "Run job on this computer" to go on.

10. Plug out AC to start Energy Efficiency job when "Disconnect AC power to start the job" appears in "Idle Energy Efficiency assessment" interface.

11. When training test completed, plug in AC and charge to 100%, then navigate to C:\data\Asmt and run RunJobABLTrained.cmd as Administrator.  

12. Ensure no warnings under the "Important information about running this job"

13. When show "Assessment Launcher - New job1", click the "Run job on this computer" to go on.  

14. Plug out AC to start Energy Efficiency job when "Disconnect AC power to start the job" appears in "Idle Energy Efficiency assessment" interface.  

15. When test completely , then run "C:/data/amd64/WAC.exe" as Administrator


 

16. When show "windows assessment Console", click "Options"->click "Open results".

17. When popup "Select Results" interface, click "Import".

18. When show "Import Results", click "Browse" and select the results folder->click "Next".

19.When show "Import results completed successfully", click "Finish".

20.Select imported results in C:\data\Asmt\result "Select Results" interface, and click "Open".

21.When results appear, record the result to CER test report.

22. Web Browsing: Duration (hrs) 

Make sure the result meet the SPEC.


If the first data does not meet SPEC, you can test three times, choose the best result.
 
Section : Battery recharge (60) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :

Note: The project which is feature PC should meet battery charge level more than 80% after one hour of charging during enter Standby or Modern Srandby.
Note: Turn on Quick Charge if supported when run Battery Recharge time test.
1. Power mode is default (Better Performance).

2. Unzip New Battery Manager test tool to C driver.

3. Discharge battery to <5%.

System will be auto shutdown.

4. Plug in AC and power on to desktop.

5. Plug in AC and make system enter in S3/MS.

6.Wait 1hour and resume the unit.

7.Open CMD with administrator than input "powercfg batteryreport" to see batteryreport.

7.1 Battery charge level(%)

Make sure the result meet the SPEC.
